## Godot-Specific Patterns

### Current Architecture (Post–NetworkX Revert)
- **Game state is pure GDScript.** Single source of truth: **territory nodes + MetaData** (unit_count, owner_id, neighbors from `territory_connections.json`). No Python, no PythonBridge, no NetworkX.
- **Movement:** Only **direct neighbors** (`is_neighbor()`). Multi-land movement was reverted; logic to re-add it in GDScript (BFS + `is_adjacent`) is saved in **`docs/networkx_overhaul/networkx_revert.md`**.
- **Export:** One-click Export All works; no Python backend, no PyInstaller, no per-platform backend builds.
- **Bots:** Use territory nodes / map (e.g. `get_owner_id()`, `get_unit_count()`, neighbor data from MetaData or map), not Python.
- The NetworkX/Python overhaul was reverted for simplicity; re-apply instructions (GDScript-only multi-land, tutorial queue) live in the doc above.

### RPC Authority Patterns
- Server authority for all game state changes (combat, turn management)
- Client prediction with server confirmation for responsive UI
- Comprehensive error handling for network edge cases

### Territory System Architecture
- MetaData nodes for clean game state separation
- Event-driven updates rather than polling for performance
- Modular territory scenes with shared script logic

### Attack of Despair System Architecture
- Global flag (`Globals.ATTACK_OF_DESPAIR`) for state management
- Server-side validation for AoD combat rules
- Client synchronization via RPC (`sync_attack_of_despair`)
- Phase integration prevents exploitation of desperate mechanics

### Elimination System Architecture
- `_handle_player_elimination()` for complete elimination handling
- Turn queue management with automatic player removal
- Bonus unit awards integrated with existing unit system
- Network synchronization of elimination state across all clients

### Steam Initialization & Lobby Routing (ConnectToGlobalUser Fix)
- **Symptom**: Friends saw `simple_lobby.tscn` instead of `steam_lobby.tscn`; logs showed `ConnectToGlobalUser failed`. Worked on dev machines (Linux/Win/Mac), failed for remote friends.
- **Root cause (simple)**: App ID mismatch. Two places were forcing the wrong ID:
  1. **`project.godot`** `[steam]` had `initialization/app_id=4140450` (Playtest). GodotSteam used this before our code ran.
  2. Code had set `OS.set_environment("STEAM_APP_ID", ...)` in `_init()`, overriding Steam’s injected ID on Windows (case-insensitive env).
- **Simple solution**: No hardcoded App ID. Let Steam inject at runtime.
  - **project.godot**: `initialization/app_id=0`, `initialization/initialize_on_startup=false`.
  - **steam_manager.gd**: No `STEAM_APP_ID` constant. Before `steamInitEx()`: read `SteamAppId` env, then `STEAM_APP_ID` env, then **`steam_appid.txt`** (res:// in editor, next to exe when exported). If value came from file, set `OS.set_environment("SteamAppId", value)` so SDK uses it. Store in `Globals.STEAM_APP_ID_ATTEMPTED` for debugging (printed on both success and failure).
  - **steam_appid.txt**: Keep in project root for dev (e.g. 4407810 for Demo). Do **not** include in Steam depot; Steam injects the correct ID when launching from client.
- **Takeaway**: When Steam lobby fails for some users, check `project.godot` [steam] and env overrides first; the fix is usually “stop hardcoding, use Steam’s ID.”

### MP Bot Integration & Last Pirate Standing
- **2-player start bot**: Lobby has mandatory Bot dropdown (Greedy Boy default) in simple_lobby and steam_lobby; `Globals.MP_EXTRA_BOT_TYPE` set on Start Game. In multiplayer_scene, `_add_mp_start_bot_if_needed()` (host only) injects one bot when 2 humans; then `active_mp.sync_all_players.rpc(active_mp.players)` so guests see the bot.
- **Leaver→bot**: On human disconnect, host runs `Server._replace_human_with_bot(peer_id)`; server converts Player to BotPlayer in-place, updates `mp_manager.players[peer_id]`, then `mp_manager.sync_all_players.rpc(mp_manager.players)` so guest sees bot avatar/color.
- **Human-only victory**: Game over uses `_get_alive_human_players_in_queue()` / `_check_human_only_game_over()`; LPS popup only when one human remains (count via `is_bot` in active_mp.players).
- **LPS guards**: Early-return in `_on_player_count_changed` and `_on_mp_connection_failed_in_game` when `Server.current_phase == GAME_OVER`. Planned: also return when victory popup is visible so guest never gets LPS after host leaves post-victory.
- **Card count sync**: After elimination transfer, `await update_player_card_count(eliminator_player_id)`; `_sync_all_player_card_counts()` at game start and on turn change for robust guest counts.
- **Combat display**: All child Control nodes need `mouse_filter = 2` for click-through (root alone is not enough).

### HUD game event log (combat + majors)
- **`HUD/event_log.gd`**: Newest-at-top (`push_front` per row), BBCode + lobby colors from active MP manager; server-only content via **`rpc_push_game_event_segments`** / **`rpc_push_game_event_line`** on **`multiplayer_scene.gd`**.
- **Combat tick buffer**: During **`_resolve_combat_on_server`**, **`_push_secondary_or_immediate_segments`** buffers continent / elimination (etc.); flush after building **`combat_segments`**.
- **Order invariant**: Because the log is **`push_front`**, push **combat first**, then each buffered row — so **continent / elimination appear above the combat line** (they are newer in the list). Width under mission: **`mission_width * 0.8`** in **`_update_avatar_scale()`**.

This project intelligence helps maintain consistency with user preferences and successful patterns discovered through collaborative development.